<p>Stripping out part of Rails’ security features is often a <a href="http://www.catb.org/jargon/html/B/Bad-Thing.html">Bad Thing</a> and shouldn’t be done unless you’re really sure you don’t need them. <em>Rails’ default configuration is sane and promotes security for most uses.</em> Don’t follow the advice in this article blindly!</p>
